<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851R.50/29</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of Staff, United States
                                    Army (<persName type="from">Marshall</persName>), to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-31">December 31,
                                        1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The following paragraph is quoted from a personal letter received
                                this morning from General Eisenhower: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“This morning I received your telegram concerning the
                                        functions of the State Department in developing the economy
                                        of this particular theater. I agree with every word of it
                                        and I can assure you that no trouble whatsoever will occur
                                        in the execution of the plan. I shall be obliged if you will
                                        assure the Secretary of State of my desire to assist him in
                                        every possible way. The sooner I can get rid of all these
                                        questions that are outside the military in scope, the
                                        happier I will be! Sometimes I think I live ten years each
                                        week, of which at least nine are absorbed in political and
                                        economic matters.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>G. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>